<item>
            <title>[LU-7803] sanity test 78 failures in interop</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7803</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Addition of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2049&quot; title=&quot;add support for OBD_CONNECT_GRANT_PARAM&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2049&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2049&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7793&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7793&lt;/a&gt; seems to be breaking interop in particular test 78 of sanity.sh so I filing this ticket just in case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am testing with upstream client, but 2.5 and 2.7 at the very least are likely affected, possibly even 2.8, so we need to double check.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the patch in place on the server, client running test 78 fails on the 5th iteration like this:&lt;br/&gt;
directIO rdwr round 5 of 5&lt;br/&gt;
directio on /mnt/lustre/f78.sanity for 130x1048576 bytes &lt;br/&gt;
Write error Success (rc = 83886080, len = 136314880)&lt;br/&gt;
 sanity test_78: @@@@@@ FAIL: rdwr failed &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This suggests the write was short due to overzealous limitation of free space on the server or something else.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I confirmed that removing that patch fixes the failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;additional issue - test 78 does not cleanup the big file on error leading to a chain of out of space failures later on in the sanity.sh at least in my setup&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is on ldiskfs&lt;/p&gt;</description>
